\": { ... }, \"clientId\": string }\n{ \"type\": \"ack\", \"version\": number }\n{ \"type\": \"error\", \"message\": string }\n```\n\n## OT Engine\n\nServer-authoritative OT with transform functions:\n- `transformOp(opA, opB)` - Transform op A against op B\n- Server maintains operation history per document\n- Incoming ops are transformed against all ops since client's base version\n- Transformed op is applied, stored, and broadcast\n\n### Transform Rules\n- Insert vs Insert: adjust positions based on relative ordering\n- Insert vs Delete: adjust positions accounting for deleted range\n- Delete vs Insert: adjust positions and potentially split delete\n- Delete vs Delete: handle overlapping ranges\n\n## Persistence\n\n- All document changes persisted to SQLite immediately\n- Version history saved with each operation\n- Document content updated in-place after each op\n- On restart, documents load from DB; version counter resumes\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
